WEBVTT

00:02.235 --> 00:05.205
[jazz music]

00:05.238 --> 00:12.278
♪ ♪

00:20.453 --> 00:22.322
[cheers and applause]

00:22.355 --> 00:23.890
- From the Penn & Teller
Theater

00:23.923 --> 00:26.059
at the Rio Hotel
in Las Vegas,

00:26.092 --> 00:30.463
here's our host,
Alyson Hannigan!

00:30.497 --> 00:32.465
[cheers and applause]

00:32.499 --> 00:39.539
♪ ♪

00:42.475 --> 00:45.678
- Tonight, our magicians
will climb into the ring

00:45.712 --> 00:48.615
and try to drop
the flying elbow of illusion

00:48.648 --> 00:51.684
right between the eyes
of our magic ring masters.

00:51.718 --> 00:54.988
Can they body slam their way
to a "Fool Us" trophy?

00:55.021 --> 00:58.691
Or, will they be stopped
by a pile driver of proof?

00:58.725 --> 01:02.429
Now, give it up for our
enchanted tag team champions,

01:02.462 --> 01:04.364
Penn and Teller!

01:04.397 --> 01:06.366
[cheers and applause]

01:06.399 --> 01:09.369
[jazz music]

01:09.402 --> 01:16.443
♪ ♪

01:20.013 --> 01:22.015
Wow.

01:22.048 --> 01:24.684
Remember, if Penn and Teller
get fooled,

01:24.717 --> 01:28.388
they give away a slot in their
world-famous magic show,

01:28.421 --> 01:32.158
a classy trophy, and
international bragging rights.

01:32.192 --> 01:35.328
With that in mind,
let's meet our first performer.

01:37.530 --> 01:40.233
- I heard the saying that
nothing makes math sexier

01:40.266 --> 01:42.569
than a board game
or a magic trick,

01:42.602 --> 01:44.070
and I completely agree.

01:44.104 --> 01:45.705
I do a show called
"Super Nerd,"

01:45.738 --> 01:47.440
which features magic, mystery,

01:47.474 --> 01:49.676
and recreational mathematics.

01:49.709 --> 01:51.644
Yeah, I'm definitely
a super nerd.

01:51.678 --> 01:53.012
I love all things nerdy.

01:53.046 --> 01:54.714
I'm not a full-time magician,

01:54.747 --> 01:56.616
and I've never
actually wanted to be.

01:56.649 --> 01:58.952
Because I don't rely on magic
for my income,

01:58.985 --> 02:00.820
my friend and I
started a charity

02:00.854 --> 02:03.490
which allows us to perform
the shows we want to perform,

02:03.523 --> 02:06.526
but all the money goes to
charities we want to support.

02:06.559 --> 02:08.595
Creating the trick
I'm here to do tonight

02:08.627 --> 02:11.531
has been a bit like playing
a "Fool Us" board game.

02:11.564 --> 02:12.832
Hopefully, Penn and Teller
like board games

02:12.866 --> 02:13.833
as much as I do,

02:13.867 --> 02:16.069
because tonight,
I came to play.

02:16.102 --> 02:19.139
[cheers and applause]

02:21.007 --> 02:25.278
- Please welcome Caleb Wiles!

02:25.311 --> 02:26.880
- I've been preparing
for this show

02:26.913 --> 02:28.715
in an interesting way.

02:28.748 --> 02:32.452
Every night, I sit in my room
and I play a board game.

02:32.485 --> 02:34.354
A very specific board game,

02:34.387 --> 02:36.389
one that I actually
created myself.

02:36.422 --> 02:38.158
And I brought that game
along with me tonight

02:38.191 --> 02:39.826
to share with all of you.

02:39.859 --> 02:43.463
I call it "Penn & Teller:
Fool Us, Home Edition."

02:43.496 --> 02:44.964
[laughter]

02:44.998 --> 02:46.799
Alyson, would you like to play?
- Sure!

02:46.833 --> 02:48.902
- Let's give her a round
of applause!

02:48.935 --> 02:51.604
[cheers and applause]
Thank you, Alyson!

02:51.638 --> 02:54.674
Now, Alyson, the set up
to this game is very simple.

02:54.707 --> 02:58.178
We just need to decide
on a target playing card.

02:58.211 --> 03:00.914
Now if you're playing at home,
you can do this at random,

03:00.947 --> 03:02.815
but since we have
Penn and Teller here,

03:02.849 --> 03:05.885
I thought maybe they could help
us decide on the target card.

03:05.919 --> 03:07.253
So, Teller, in a moment,

03:07.287 --> 03:09.822
I'm gonna ask you
to choose a value.

03:09.856 --> 03:11.658
Penn, you will choose a suit,

03:11.691 --> 03:13.526
and together,
we will combine your choices

03:13.560 --> 03:16.696
to create a card that no one
could've possibly known.

03:16.729 --> 03:18.798
Teller, what value
would you like?

03:21.801 --> 03:24.837
A king?
A king, and Penn, the suit.

03:24.871 --> 03:27.407
- Spades.
- The king of spades,

03:27.440 --> 03:28.808
that will be our target card.

03:28.841 --> 03:31.978
Now, Alyson, the object
of this game is to find that

03:32.011 --> 03:34.480
target card in a magic trick,
that's how you win.

03:34.514 --> 03:35.882
- Okay.
- Okay, and in fact

03:35.915 --> 03:37.850
if you find
the King of spades tonight,

03:37.884 --> 03:41.054
I guarantee, you will go home
with the trophy.

03:41.087 --> 03:43.623
- Hey, I like it.
- Yeah.

03:43.656 --> 03:46.092
[cheers and applause]

03:46.125 --> 03:47.493
- Well, that's because
I 3-D printed

03:47.527 --> 03:49.862
one "Fool Us" trophy myself.

03:49.896 --> 03:51.898
- Aww, that's pretty cute.

03:51.931 --> 03:54.167
I'd take it.

03:54.200 --> 03:56.169
I would definitely take it.

03:56.202 --> 03:57.837
- Now, Alyson, inside this box

03:57.870 --> 03:59.739
is literally everything we need

03:59.772 --> 04:02.075
to play a game
of "Fool Us" at home.

04:02.108 --> 04:04.444
For example,
I have the official

04:04.477 --> 04:07.814
"Penn & Teller:
Fool Us, Home Edition"

04:07.847 --> 04:10.083
deck of playing cards.
- Aw.

04:10.116 --> 04:12.485
- And inside this deck
of playing cards,

04:12.518 --> 04:15.255
I have two very special jokers.

04:15.288 --> 04:18.358
These are jokers
you'll actually recognize.

04:18.391 --> 04:22.729
As we spread the pack,
you'll see there's Penn.

04:22.762 --> 04:24.097
- Mm, Big joker.

04:24.130 --> 04:26.165
- And there's Teller.
- Aww.

04:27.200 --> 04:29.168
- Now if we have
Penn and Teller,

04:29.202 --> 04:30.370
you know what else
we need, Alyson.

04:30.403 --> 04:31.804
- What?
- We need the official

04:31.838 --> 04:36.242
"Penn & Teller: Fool Us,
Home Edition" judges' chairs.

04:36.276 --> 04:38.177
- Aww.

04:38.211 --> 04:40.947
- You see, this is
where Penn and Teller

04:40.980 --> 04:43.583
will sit to watch your trick.

04:43.616 --> 04:47.820
And at the end, maybe, they'll
tell us what they think.

04:47.854 --> 04:50.790
My favorite component
is actually the official

04:50.823 --> 04:54.427
"Penn & Teller:
Fool Us, Home Edition" stage.

04:54.460 --> 04:55.995
- Ohh.

04:56.029 --> 04:59.365
- Yes, 'cause this is where
we display the trophy, yes.

04:59.399 --> 05:02.935
And just like in the real show,
the trophy...

05:02.969 --> 05:05.538
- Oh, yeah.
- Hangs high up in the air.

05:05.571 --> 05:09.108
- Aww.

05:09.142 --> 05:10.243
- And remember, Alyson,

05:10.276 --> 05:12.078
if you find
that King of spades,

05:12.111 --> 05:14.080
that trophy belongs to you.

05:14.113 --> 05:15.882
- Well, I'm going home
with that trophy.

05:15.915 --> 05:18.418
- Now that the stage is set.
