17:45.330 --> 17:47.032
- Aww.
- Yeah.

17:47.066 --> 17:51.837
- Well, that's lovely.

17:51.870 --> 17:53.205
All right, Penn and Teller

17:53.238 --> 17:54.907
have had enough time
to think it over,

17:54.940 --> 17:57.109
so let's see
if you fooled them.

17:57.142 --> 17:58.210
Guys!

17:58.243 --> 18:00.879
- D.K., what a great routine.

18:00.913 --> 18:03.916
Just loved it.
Really loved it.

18:03.949 --> 18:06.185
And, you know...
[applause]

18:06.218 --> 18:08.587
with that kind of

18:08.620 --> 18:11.290
high-concept,
beautiful thing,

18:11.323 --> 18:14.259
you're almost guaranteed
for Teller to like it.

18:14.293 --> 18:16.195
That's the kind
of thing Teller loves.

18:16.228 --> 18:19.364
Teller's the kind of child
that walked around his room

18:19.398 --> 18:23.435
with a flashlight, and objects
and looking at them.

18:23.469 --> 18:25.370
I'm not that kind of child.

18:25.404 --> 18:27.573
That's the kind of stuff
that you were doing,

18:27.606 --> 18:30.943
kind of stuff that
categorically I don't like.

18:30.976 --> 18:32.311
I love this.

18:32.344 --> 18:35.481
And you're able to do
something that thoughtful,

18:35.514 --> 18:37.449
that perfectly laid out,

18:37.483 --> 18:39.818
and still not
have it feel pretentious,

18:39.852 --> 18:43.122
and that is a huge
magic trick in itself.

18:43.155 --> 18:45.190
It's not precious.

18:45.224 --> 18:47.659
It's just beautiful.

18:47.693 --> 18:49.761
And that line
is hard to draw.

18:49.795 --> 18:51.163
[applause]

18:51.196 --> 18:53.232
And, um...

18:55.300 --> 18:58.837
the routine used
mechanical stuff,

18:58.871 --> 19:03.142
it used science,
it used raw sleight-of-hand,

19:03.175 --> 19:07.513
it used this genius move
of having the screen

19:07.546 --> 19:10.849
being necessary
to cause the magic,

19:10.883 --> 19:14.553
and also necessary
to accomplish the magic.

19:14.586 --> 19:17.656
